# Investigator Protocol

Read when: worker returned BLOCKED twice on the same Path ID, cloud review hits ESCALATE, test honesty failed, or a shipped packet caused a visible regression.
Skip when: regular DONE review, first BLOCKED, or routine lint/test repair.

Purpose: higher-tier cloud debugging role for problems the orchestrator + local worker cannot resolve safely.

## When To Invoke
- Worker returned BLOCKED >= 2 times on same Path ID
- Root cause unclear after post-coding review
- Test-honesty failure detected
- Production or real-use regression after acceptance
- Architectural decision required that was not in the spec

Do not invoke for:
- First BLOCKED
- Routine DONE acceptance
- Formatting/lint/type cleanup
- Local runtime outage, model download, reboot, or unreachable local worker

## Investigator Packet
```text
INVESTIGATOR PACKET
- Origin Packet ID: P-YYYY-MM-DD-NN
- Spec ID: SPEC-NN-name or none
- Failure Mode: REPEATED-BLOCKED | TEST-HONESTY | PROD-REGRESSION | ARCH-UNCLEAR
- Path IDs in scope:
- Files investigator may read:
- Files investigator may modify: none | listed files | direct-fix allowed
- Question to answer:
- Required output: ROOT-CAUSE | NEW-WORKER-PACKET | DIRECT-FIX | SPEC-AMENDMENT
```

## Output Modes

### ROOT-CAUSE
Return analysis plus corrected worker packet. Normal flow resumes.

### NEW-WORKER-PACKET
Decompose into smaller packets. Worker runs them sequentially.

### DIRECT-FIX
Cloud investigator makes the change directly only when:
- fix is small,
- local worker has failed at this category,
- direct fix is cheaper/safer than another worker loop.

Still update traceability and run apply/review gates.

### SPEC-AMENDMENT
Original feature/spec was wrong. Return amended spec and restart decomposition.

### TIE-BREAKER-HALT
Use when investigator and worker fail to resolve the same BLOCKED status after two full investigator cycles, or when the disagreement depends on environment quirks the models cannot verify.

Return a plain-English operator summary instead of another worker packet:
- What the worker believes
- What the investigator believes
- What evidence supports each side
- Lowest-risk pause point
- Three operator choices with risk/cost labels

Do not issue a third investigator-derived packet without explicit human choice.

## Cost And Use Limits
- Track every invocation in ledger/session budget if enabled.
- If investigator use becomes frequent, stop and retune packet quality or local-worker model.
- Do not use investigator to debug infrastructure outage.
- After two investigator cycles on the same Path ID, return TIE-BREAKER-HALT and update `docs/OPERATOR_DASHBOARD.md`.
